<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  appcast.xml — the LIVE Sparkle update feed for Airlive Bridge.

  Served free and permanently by GitHub at:
    https://raw.githubusercontent.com/airlive-project/airlive-bridge/main/appcast.xml
  (this exact URL is baked into every shipped build via SUFeedURL — never move
  or rename this file).  The .dmg itself is served by GitHub Releases (the
  enclosure url); this file only announces versions.

  Per release, add one <item>:
    <item>
      <title>Airlive Bridge X.Y.Z</title>
      <pubDate>…RFC 822 date…</pubDate>
      <sparkle:version>N</sparkle:version>                 CFBundleVersion (the integer Sparkle compares)
      <sparkle:shortVersionString>X.Y.Z</sparkle:shortVersionString>
      <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>13.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
      <enclosure
        url="https://github.com/airlive-project/airlive-bridge/releases/download/vX.Y.Z/Airlive-Bridge-X.Y.Z.dmg"
        length="…"  type="application/octet-stream"
        sparkle:edSignature="…" />
    </item>
  `length` + `sparkle:edSignature` come from `sign_update` on the FINAL
  notarized+stapled .dmg (package.sh prints them).  Keep the enclosure url ==
  the uploaded GitHub asset name == the file package.sh produces.

  No <item> entries = every installed build is up to date (valid feed).
-->
